  "body": "Suppose I am making a custom radio button field that shows up like a bunch of toggleable-buttons:\n\n``` cjsx\n<ButtonToggle name=\"fileType\">\n    <Option value=\"readme\"   title=\"README\" />\n    <Option value=\"starter\"  title=\"Starter\" />\n    <Option value=\"solution\" title=\"Solution\" />\n</ButtonToggle>\n```\n\nEach of the `Option` components will render as a `button` wrapping a hidden `<input type=\"radio\">`.\n\nThe input needs to use the name from the parent `ButtonToggle` component, but there's no clear way how to correctly transfer the prop automatically.\n\nIt seems redundant to set the `name` prop on each `Option` individually.\n\nHowever, if I use `React.Children.forEach` to iterate over the children in the `ButtonToggle`'s `render()` method, the objects I get are `ReactElements`, which do not have a `setProps()` method. Instead I did this:\n\n``` cjsx\nButtonToggle = React.createClass\n  render: ->\n    React.Children.forEach @props.children, (option) =>\n      # XXX I have no idea if this is OK... no setProps() available\n      option.props.name = @props.name\n\n    <div className=\"ui buttons\">\n      { @props.children }\n    </div>\n```\n\nIs this an anti-pattern/bug? If not, perhaps it should be added to the docs.\n",
